                <div class="text-break text-md">Job Description A vacancy has become available for a Multi Skilled Assessor within the North-West Province. As the OUTsurance Claims Assessor (Multi-skilled) you will be responsible for assessing, validating and finalising personal lines and business claims. Minimum Requirements. Applicant should reside in the North-West Province Experience: Investigation/Assessing experience, especially in a short-term insurance industry Client service experience. Applicant must be able to speak and understand Tswana &amp; Afrikaans. Responsibilities: Validate all incidents and claims Meeting with clients, witnesses, SAPS and all other law enforcement officials, towing operators etc. Finalise all reports and administration (reports, scanning, photographs etc.) Liaise with service providers Make the decision, all administration and telephonic queries arising around that. Handling and resolving all queries and problems from service provider and clients. Conduct all the above to the required performance and quality standards that are in place. Be able to draft reports when the need arises.</div>
